==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|arrayen|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|xno|en}} {{term|arayer|lang=fro}} (compare {{etyl|fro|-}} {{term|arayer|lang=fro}}, {{term|areer||to put in order|lang=fro}}), from {{etyl|ML.|en}} {{term/t|la|arrēdō||to put in order, arrange, array}}, from {{etyl|ML.|en}} {{term/t|la|*rēdum||preparation, order}}, from {{etyl|frk|en}} {{term/t|frk|*reida||preparation, order}} or {{etyl|got|en}} {{term|𐌲𐌰𐍂𐌰𐌹𐌳𐍃||tr=garaids|ready, prepared|lang=got}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{term/t|gem-pro|*raidaz}}, {{term/t|gem-pro|*raidiz||ready}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{term/t|ine-pro|*reidʰ-||to put in order, ease, make comfortable}}. Cognate with {{etyl|goh|-}} {{term/t|goh|gireiti||preparation}}, {{etyl|ofs|-}} {{term|rēde||ready|lang=ofs}}, {{etyl|ang|-}} {{term/t|ang|ġerǣde||preparation, equipment}}. More at [[ready]].

